messages.content: "Yeah." Washington says glumly. "I'll go check up on my daughter, see if he hasn't confused her even more."
“Yes, you do that.” Nash says dismissively, then turns to Oswalda. “Mother, are you alright? He didn’t harass you too much, I hope?”

Washington leaves.

"Yes, we're quite alright, Nash. He just wanted to speak to the Duchess, it seems... She also went along with it." Oswalda.
Nash sighs. “Honestly, she shouldn’t endure any indignities from that man..”
"It's quite alright, Nash. I expected it." The Duchess approaches with a smirk.
Nash bows again. “Hello, mother. Glad to see your spirits are still up.”
"The baron suspected me, but it simply would not be possible. My alibi is simply much too strong." The Duchess gives an amused smile.
Nash smiles at her nervously. "Yes, that'd be... utterly ridiculous, to suspect you."
"He’s after your sister now to confirm my alibi. Everything should be resolved then."
"Gh..." Nash says. "Is it really necessary for him to talk to Kori?"

"I was with Kori most of the night... She meants Harriet Dana." Oswalda.

"Yes, that's correct. Kori was missing for a period, but she is a child. She could not have committed murder." The Duchess.
Nash's eye twitches, again. "Right. Harriet." He crosses his arms and pouts, childishly.
"You have many other siblings, Nash. Don't play favorites. I certainly don't." The Duchess laughs politely.
"I'm not-!" Nash starts, then stops himself. "...I apologize. Yes, you're correct."
"We still love you, Nash..." Oswalda.
"I know that!" He snaps. "I know, that was.. never in question.."
"Shouldn't you be at work, anyway?" The Duchess.
Nash forces a smile. "Yes, I.. I've been assigned to investigate what's happened to the Emperor."
*Praise me, won't you? ...I've shown initiative.*
"Oh? And who did?" The Duchess.
"Who assigned me..? Triden himself." *The biggest name there is recognized me.*
She seems uninterested and even maybe a little disappointed in Nash. "I meant who stabbed him."

"Ah..." *Fuck. Fuck! Use context clues, idiot, she obviously doesn't care about Triden... I mean, why would she, right? His power is objectively inferior to hers, the scope of his, uh, his everything.. and he's a man, besides. Think fucking logically. Of course she just wants the answers! That's what's important. What kind of son am I, to not be able to provide that for her?* "Well, I-I'm. The investigation is still in preliminary stages, um."
"I see. Well, I didn't do it." The Duchess smiles.
"Yes, I. I know that, of course." Nash smiles up at her in return.
"Have you considered Asturian?"
Nash bites his knuckle. "I have, of course. He seems like the.. logical choice. But I've been advised against pursuing the matter."
"Did you know he refuses to let anyone visit the emperor except him? How suspicious, wouldn't you say...?"
"It *is* tremendously suspicious."
"Perhaps you ought to speak to Triden about it, if he's still able to form a coherent sentence." The Duchess says this with a casual tone, but Oswalda looks at her nervously.
Nash grins shakily. "Er, yes.. I could."
There's a knock on the door.
"Ah. Allow me to get that." Nash says, and walks to the door to open it.
It's Orion. "There you are, Nash."
Nash smiles at him. "Sorry for any delay. I got sidetracked."
"Well, I found a lead. Ruth's got the guest list too. Do you have anything?" Orion.

*Gghh... what are you doing?!? Mentioning in front of heeeeer that you found a lead.. Do you want her attention? Is that it? To prove that you're doing beeeeetter at this than me?* Nash's grin turns strained. "Er, by a certain meaning of the word..."
"We should get back to her, then. Share everything we learned."
"Yes." Nash says, trying to pull himself together, maintain composure, fucking... Yes. "I'll see you later, Mother." He says to The Duchess.
"Of course. Later, Nash."
He follows Orion out the door.
Orion heads back to the castle. Again.
Ruth is waiting for them by the door to the basement.
Nash walks to her. "Are we going down?" He gestures to the door.

"Right, so... According to witnesses, this door should've been locked at the party, right?" Orion grabs the doorhandle. "And no one has touched it since the Emperor was stabbed. And yet..." Orion casually opens the door.
"Someone must've been sneaking around the castle. Possibly someone who wasn't supposed to be at the party."
Nash frowns, hand to his chin. "If they weren't supposed to be on the party, though, the guestlist won't help us, right?"

"I still doubt it was someone from outside." Ruth.

"But if it was, we can basically use the guest list to eliminate suspects. We just need confirmation." Orion.
"It's still ultimately speculation." Nash nods. "I don't think we can say that just because someone was sneaking around means that they weren't invited in the first place."

"Let's just investigate for now." Orion heads down.

"Who made him the boss?" Ruth groans and descends.

Nash coughs, loudly and unsubtly, at Orion taking charge. *I don't know what he thinks he's doing, honestly. Just placing himself at the frontlines.. a woeful act of self-endangerment.* His lip curls. But he doesn't do anything about it.
Nash follows.
They are now in the basement. ((Roll investigation to look around))
((Nat 1, actually))
Nash's amazing castle navigation skills cause him to lock himself in a room.
"GAH!" He yelps.
"I've, uh, navigated myself into a predicament..."
He is alone.
Wehh....
What's the inside of the room like?

It's some kind of abandoned servant room. There are beds and other fixtures of a servant room, but the door's lock appears to have rusted from lack of use and is now stuck as locked. The room is very dusty.
Hm. Nash attempts to investigate the room. Surely this will go better than the last time he tried.
It is a normal servant room. There's nothing hidden around.
How annoying...
Are there any other doors? Or is it just the one leading out?
Just the one.
Nash bangs on the door loudly.
((Roll strength ig))
Ruth breaks the door down. "There you are."
Nash yelps, leaping unsubtly out of the way of her. "I'm not sure how this happened. Honest."
"Whatever. I found something."
"Oh?"
"Follow me." She walks off.
He follows.
They arrive at a random dead end wall. Ruth just punches it for some reason.
Ruth then punches another wall, which causes the bricks it is made of to crack a bit. "That's not a normal wall."
Nash examines it. "For sure. Certainly not made out of reinforced concrete. Plaster, maybe..?"
"It's possible... But they wouldn't go through that effort for no reason."
"For sure." Nash nods. "Need my assistance?"
"You got any useful magic?"
He frowns. "I can attempt to smite it.. but that might cause a fire. Willing to risk it, ma'am?" He says the last part with a semi-mocking drawl.
"It's brick." She affords 0 further thought to what could set fire.
Nash raises an eyebrow. "Alright, then. I'll give it a go."
Nash casts Searing Smite. ((do i need to roll to hit i mean it's a wall))
The wall is struck. Nothing happens.
"Annoying." Nash huffs. "We could just keep hitting it..?"
"It might be magic?"
"Hmm... That'd be problematic."
"Yeah. But we’ve got the jurisdiction, so…" She runs back down the hall.
Nash follows.
She goes into the room that would essentially be the wall next door and begins trying to break down the wall.
Nash. Assists.
((Roll damage))
((Yeah))
The wall is only slightly harmed. They keep hitting it.
Nash hits again.
((Roll damage))
They finally create a decent enough hole in the wall to slip through. Ruth goes in.
Nash follows.

They arrive at what looks like the interior of some safe. The strange wall from earlier contains a door from this side. There’s another, larger, hole in the wall across from the door. In the center, propped up inside some kind of broken display case, is a gem that is glowing black.
"That... looks concerning." Nash externalizes.
Ruth slowly approaches the gem.
Nash does as well, while kind-of hiding behind her.

She grabs it, causing it to immediately crumble. 

A magical construct of a suit of armour begins to form in the room. "Intruders detected. The sunslayer must be defended."

((End session because I’m eepy. Combat next time))
Erik and Selle are standing in the catacombs.

Selle is in a cold sweat, panting with their hand to their head, both still tired from the fight and having barely escaped.
"That was way too close... Agh..."
"Who the hell was that?"
"That was the High Priestess of the Order of Libra, and a bunch of the priests."

"Fuck... Locruz didn't manage to make it with us. They are definitely going to do something with him, if he's even alive... Dammit! He's just a kid, why does he need to be involved in all this bullshit? Why is our society so fucked, and rotten to the core that people like him or me get our lives stolen and kept hostage by rot and greed and the constant struggle to not get caught up in the worst things that can possibly happen. Fuck!!" 
Selle bangs the wall of the catacomb with their fist.
Erik sighs. "You've got some wacky priests here. Any idea why she was after you?"

"There could be multiple reasons... Asturian is the Emperor now, and he's obsessed with outlawing everything to do with magic or mutants... I'm both a prominent magic user and I'm disabled in my right arm due to my illness which makes me a target...  Second, since I wasn't disguised, there's a chance that they have caught onto me and branded me a heretic, since I've written multiple illegal pieces that criticise the Order and call out scandals in it. Either way, it's not good, and we were lucky I had that spell scroll on me... The fact that I was undisguised is a really a big mistake on my behalf..."
"So you’re some kind of atheist celebrity?" He chuckles.
"I don't know if I'm famous enough to be a celebrity..." Selle sighs. "I'm just someone who can't stand the way the world is, and I want to do something with my existence that's for good."

"How does the atheism thing work? I mean... Priests, paladins, clerics... All those holy guys do have powers. Which raises a few new questions about the hatred for magic and other religions, but whatever... Where's that power come from in your head?"

"My power, and, everyone's power for that matter is just from magic techniques that they learn. To me, "atheism" is just a means to an end of ending the oppressive hierarchy of the Order, where people use their skill of magic, from talent or from hard work, to make others obey them by proclaiming themselves as those who serve a higher power. It's a vicious cycle of hypocrisy."
"...Gotcha." ((Roll insight))
He seems to find this funny rather than a serious perspective.
"...Whatever, it doesn't matter. Has any of your memory returned?"
"Of sorts. Everything is slowly coming back, but nothing you haven't already learned without it yet."
"I see..." Selle sighs. "We need a way to relay the information we got to Donald."
"These are the catacombs, right?"
"Yeah. It's fairly dangerous in here if you don't know your way around but there are safe paths."
"We should be especially careful of that monster if it's down here."

Selle nods.
"There's a very high possibility it's down here. Let's stay on our toes"
"We're in no shape to fight it, most likely."

"That's right. And we've seen what happens to people who come across it." 
Selle shudders remembering what they saw in the bar.
"Let's get going."
"Where are we headed?"

*I'm not sure if I trust to bring Erik to Laura's base, as I know next to nothing about his identity, and it's likely going there won't help at all. We need to head somewhere where we can change our outfits and safely find a way to contact Donald.*
"Let's head outside, deeper into the undercity. We need to find a way to change our clothes. We can probably find some sort of abandoned building. After that, we can try and look for Donald."
"...No. I'm out of power here. We need to find somewhere to rest before we can do anything."

*That's true...*
"Maybe we could look for a hostel or inn of some sort to stay at."
Erik checks his pockets, finding nothing. "Seems like I’ve lost everything but my sword. Which is my better sword, at least."
"It must've not gone through the Dimension Door. At least you've got a spare weapon."
"Don’t think I had it earlier either. Must be buried under all the shit at the bar."
"At least that means you can retrieve it later"
"Hopefully. But I’ve got no cash."
"I've got some on me. Not too much though."
"Well. There's one place we can go to that we might be able to rest. But I need to know if I can trust you first."
A large explosion has struck Major Iono Wilkinson's home.
“What the fuck!” I say this.
She ignores Aeolian and rushes into the building with an angry gaze.
I follow her. “You are far out of line. This is an act… this…!”

The major is unconscious on the ground. He looks injured.

"Where are they?" Harriet looks around, to no avail.
“Whoever *they* is, probably buried under rubble. Good lord.” I grimace.

"There were 2 of them. Accomplices, most likely." Harriet.

A priest approaches them dragging Locruz. "We've apprehended a core member of the hellhounds!"
“Not true.” I shake my head.
"What?" Harriet.
“What evidence are you founding this accusation on?”
"The guilt of Locruz Klezmer?" Harriet gives him a disgusted look. "It is known."
“How?”
"Do not waste my time." She magically creates restraints with ribbons of light. "Even if he were innocent, he would be our only lead to this villain who escaped."
“Harriet… are you quite sure you grasp the full ramifications of what you are doing right now?”
"That is High Priestess Edwardson to you... And I am helping secure the future of this kingdom before other nations see your response as weak."

“Edwardson, yes. Your family name. I think there are some people who might look at this situation… at the absence of an unambiguous higher-up leader, and the daughter of the Duchess invades the territory of a long-time rival of hers to extrajudicially capture one of his citizens…” I frown. “There are those who would perceive this as an act of war.”
"Well, I don't care if many are as stupid as you. I am acting upon the will of Libra."
“Whatever that means. I am acting upon the will of America. See, I can say words as well.”
"Libra is a goddess, you heretical fool."
“It’s scales.”
"Yes." She confirms this and starts leaving.

“I do not have the physical ability to stop you at the moment… I am of the sort that hones their words rather than the ability to maim and kill. But I will not be letting this go. You will not torture this boy on one of your cultish whims.”
"I do not torture. He is a criminal who shall be prosecuted. If you wish to do something of worth, you should help that dying elf." The order of libra leaves with Locruz.
“That what.” I look around.
She is referring to the major, presumably.
Oh, right. I go over and check on him.
I don’t see race.
((Roll medicine))
He could die, but Aeolian can stabilize him with that roll.
Okay, I stabilize him.
He's alive.
That is good. Is there anyone else here? There were multiple people talking, and I don’t imagine any were Locruz since I only recognized the Major’s voice…
Locruz was also in front of you when this happened. ((Roll investigation))
Aeolian finds some kind of used spell scroll. Aside from that, there's no sign of where the other 2 people went.
Mm. I examine it and see if there’s any evidence of what spell it was.
((Roll arcana ig))
It's a level 4 spell scroll, but the specific spell used can only be speculated upon.
“Intriguing.” I pocket it.
To be clear, it is not reusable. It's just crumbling paper. It falls apart in your pocket.
I wanted to pocket it for evidence, not use. Whoops.
I shake the Major awake.
"Humph...?" He looks up at Aeolian with an amused expression.
“What happened here.”
He looks around. "Must've been the wind, hm?"
“No, the building was blown up.”
He laughs weakly. "No, really?"
“Yes.”
"Weather must be crazy today." He smirks.
“No. The building was attacked by Harriet Dana Edwardson in order to perform an arrest.”
"Who do you think called her?"
“I don’t know. You?”
"Yes, that's what I was saying." He chuckles.
“Okay. I think it was bad that she almost killed you then, and would have without my intervention.”
"I see." He scoffs and props himself up against a wall. "Did you need something then?"
“Why did you call her?”
"A whim." ((Roll insight))
He is fucking with you.
“That does not make sense, now, does it?”
"Wow... You're telling me this for the first time."
“Yees.”
"Will that be all?"
“No, I would still like to know the actual reasoning.”
"Wouldn't we all?"
“Probably not anyone but me, no.”
He laughs.
“It isn’t funny. I don’t understand why this would be a secret. You can just claim you were reporting a crime.”
"Do you know just how old I am, Aeolian Burr? Everything's gotta be funny a a certain age."
“Not really. Many older people have rather narrow senses of humor.”
"Centuries, baron. I'm centuries old." He points to his elf ears.
“Okay. I’m willing to wait just a second.”
"I don't care."
“……” I stare at him.
"I've been through a lot of shit, in my life. You need to impress me to be worth my time at this stage... And you just never have."
"Would it impress you if I let you die?"
"Not particularly."
“Okay. What if I threatened your life for you to stop fucking around. Hypothetically.”
"I'd think beating on an injured old man is pretty pathetic."
“Well, yes.”
He just sits there. "Do you really have nothing better to do?'
“At the moment, no. This is my one lead and you don’t actually seem to have a serious conviction to hold back from telling me.”
"Maybe I just don't like you."
“Quite possible. I think the rational course of action in that case would be the one which gets me to leave.”
"Umm... Boss?" Theo.
“Yes?” Oh, right, he’s here.
"Why don't we just try to ask Locruz instead? This old man doesn't look like he wants to cooperate..."
“…I guess.” I nod.
"Hopefully the people at the temple are nicer than here..." Theo heads off towards the temple.
I follow. I guess. I glance back briefly at the major, annoyed.
They arrive at the entrance. "We’d like to visit a prisoner you just apprehended."
“Indeed.” I affirm his correctness.

"Denied." Priest.

"Huh!?" Theo.
“On what grounds?”
"The high priestess has demanded he be under constant surveillance until tomorrow. Please come back then!"
“Hm.” How late in the day is it?
Evening at this point.
“…Fine.” I sigh loudly.
"Sorry I wasn’t of much help, Lord Burr…" Theo.
“It’s alright. We’re up against something of an immovable wall at the moment, but…” I sigh. “Something’s got to give.”
Theo starts heading back to Aeolian's house.
I do so as well.
Aliza is at his door. "Hello."
“Good evening.” I nod.
"I heard from my father you’ve been investigating the case."
“Something like that, yes.”
"Do you have a theory yet?"

“Nothing altogether too clear. The Duchess’s ilk seem to have come to their conclusion, but I’ve not been granted their *illustrious* reasoning. The involvement of certain criminal elements seems likely, but that’s dodging the question…”
"Would you like to engage in debate combat about our conclusions?" She goes into her combat stance because friendship is bizarre for people like her.
“Certainly.” Whatever this means is perfectly reasonable.
